#X text 68 23 The object takes multichannel connections and the delay line then has different channels for each input channel. Unlike Vanilla's [delwrite~] \, there's no channels message or argument \, so whatever the number of input channels you feed into it \, then that's what you automatically get. Reading from the delay line automatically gives you the same number of channels and more more details check the help file of [del.out~]., f 67;
